included.description: Worked on several projects enhancing pilot decision making in adverse weather conditions as part of a multidisciplinary team comprised of meteorologists, engineers, and cognitive psychologists. This research was conducted in support of the Federal Aviation Administration's (FAA) Weather Technology in the Cockpit Program (WTIC). Performed usability testing, SME interviews, heuristic evaluations, competitive reviews, and experimental testing with statistical analysis.
included.title: Human Factors Researcher

included.description: Conducted several research projects optimizing websites and apps across mobile and non-mobile form factors (phone, tablet, and desktop) and all phases of the development lifecycle. Projects involved a wide set of methodologies, including concept studies, eye tracking, lab usability studies, remote usability studies, heuristic evaluations, surveys, competitive reviews, and quantitative instrumentation analytics.
included.title: User Experience Researcher

included.description: Designed and executed multiple empirical and computational investigations into the impact of memorial and attentional processes underlying human decision making as lead researcher on a 3-year grant from the National Science Foundation. This work utilized a wide array of methodologies, such as eye tracking, electroencephalography (EEG), and computational simulation modeling of human memory and decision making resulting in several novel insights highlighting the utility of understanding decision making as reliant upon fundamental memory processes.
included.title: Postdoctoral Research Fellow

included.description: Developed and executed numerous projects investigating various aspects of human cognition, primarily in the domains of memory, visual attention, and decision making. I also designed and instructed courses on statistical methods for classroom and online formats. Proposed and was awarded a 3-year research grant from the National Science Foundation based on the preliminary findings of my dissertation work.
